             </li></span><span class="shcut-g" id="attack_sngs_4"> <h2 class="shcut" hclass="shcut" id="attack_shcut_4" htag="h2">action to stop something</h2><li class="sense" htag="li" sensenum="8" id="attack_sng_4" hclass="sense"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="grammar" hclass="grammar" htag="span">[countable]</span></span> <span class="cf" htag="span" hclass="cf">attack (on something)</span> <span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">an action that you take to try to stop or change something that you feel is bad</span><ul class="examples" hclass="examples" htag="ul"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">to <span class="cl">launch an</span> all-out <span class="cl">attack</span> on poverty/unemployment</span></li></ul>      </li></span><span class="shcut-g" id="attack_sngs_7"> <h2 class="shcut" id="attack_shcut_7" hclass="shcut" htag="h2">damage</h2><li class="sense" sensenum="9" bord="y" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="attack_sng_7"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="grammar" htag="span" hclass="grammar">[uncountable, countable]</span></span> <span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">the action of something such as an insect, or a disease, that causes damage to something/somebody</span><ul class="examples" hclass="examples" htag="ul"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">The roof timbers were affected by rot and insect attack.</span></li></ul>      </li></span><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" unbox="wordorigin" id="attack_unbox_7"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">early 17th cent.: from French <span class="ei">attaque</span> (noun), <span class="ei">attaquer</span> (verb), from Italian <span class="ei">attacco</span> ‘an attack’, <span class="ei">attaccare</span> ‘join battle’, based on an element of Germanic origin (see <span class="eb">attach</span>).</span></span></span></div></ol><span class="dictlink-g"><span clas